This README.md reflects the functionnalities necessary for each modules.  

## Common capabilties to all providers
- Generate SSH keys
- n numbers of masters and n numbers of workers
- Add or remove VMs 
- Separate masters/workers objects
- Per-role:
    - CPU / RAM / disk
    - optional IP/MAC
    - extra disks (structured)
- Cloud-init choice:
    - Set username for a root priviled user with its ssh pub key
- Optional vars pass to cloud-init:
  - k3s
  - rke2
  - Specific to k3s/rke2:
      - Generating a Token
      - Pulling Kubeconfig
  - ansible-pull

## Specific Azure model
- NSG rules 

## Specific Libvirt model
- Per-role:
    - optional IP/MAC
- Network config
    - NAT or Bridge
    - DHCP or Static

## Specific OVH model